				<td colspan="2"><span>There are so many obvious things they could have addresses and havent. Im not sure why they will do anything now. look at our cap issue. We have to get very rare items to break the cap (much more rare than caster focus items) and then buy AA to make them useable. it has been argued that casters have to buy AA to get their crits but so do we (add up all our melee crits dot crits and spell crits) so I just cant see how this holds. The missed notes issue has never been officially settled and we dont know if they are gonna take the MOTP solution away or not. DPS issue has never been addressed even and if it wasnt for the lack of people playing it would make us a lot more udesireable for things like MPG trials. How can they not realize that our epic was unbalanced to begin with and now that their are fewer people on what is the chance tht a bard who could actually benefit from an epic is actually ever going to get one? If they need us to point these things out to them they are just frigging clueless.
<br />

<br />
       As a bard who has recently entered the EP's it seems that my resists are only occasionally of value, i can pull but so can monks and rangers and SK's, my CC abilities are so so and my DPS sux. My DS are puny compared to the mobs we fight and my mitigation seems awfully sucky for a plate class. i still have the mana song which we still need and I think the AC boost I give may help (still not sure about Niv's with its rune effect). I still enjoy getting together with my friends though so I will stay play a bit longer and certainly in a group situation i can fill in if there is a missing class. I am just skeptical that anything will be done when some of these issues have never been addressed at all.
<br />

<br />
Rinludar</span></td>
