				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Top 10 Issue<a name="71454"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 23 04 10:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't really want to admit that I've thrown in the towel just yet, but, lately, I'm finding many more reasons not to play (for all the reasons y'all have listed above and more).  I'm finding it harder and harder to actually convince myself to log on in the evenings anymore.
<br />

<br />
I'm just not sure that the &quot;grind&quot; is worth it anymore.  I've seen many others' posts on this board whom seem to share this sentiment (maybe to slightly more or lesser extents).  In the past 2-3 weeks, I've spent about 1-2 hours total on eq (helping a long time friend finish the 8th Coldain shawl).  I can't really say I've missed the game all that much.  That makes me a bit sad to say, but it's the truth.
<br />

<br />
From my perspective, and I'd classify myself just on the casual side of being a devoted eq player, the game started losing appeal (for me) around the GoD timeframe.  It has steadily gone downhill since then (OoW'ish timeframe).  I thouroughly enjoyed all previous expansions, but I can't really make that same claim (with any measureable conviction) for the GoD and OoW expansions.  I feel that my bard's value-add to my groups has decreased exponentially.  The bigest thing I bring to my groups now is my ability to pull well.  I'm just not sure that's enough anymore.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
