				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Top 10 Issue<a name="71499"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 25 04 3:08 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The usefulness of a bard in comparison to another class is completely relative to where you're fighting.  These days, the server population in general and of bards in specific is so low that we don't run into too many, but still many bard roles are unnecessary at the top end.
<br />

<br />
As melee DPS increasers, overhaste still improves things, but not as much as adding another melee class in our place.  The value of additional ATK has diminishing returns past a certain level and when all of your melees have 2500 ATK, adding 250 more isn't helping much.  
<br />

<br />
As caster DPS increasers, I can still give Eriki's to the pet classes and it helps some.  An additional *chance* at spell damage increases is nice but it's not nice enough to warrant giving a bard a raid spot instead of another wizard.
<br />

<br />
Looking at my songs, I feel like I should have a strong contribution to the raid as a debuffer.  But in reality the dots don't land because the mobs are too resistant so I shelve them and look for something else.
<br />

<br />
One bard for AE mana is enough.
<br />

<br />
AC is nice for tanks but when your MT has 2800 AC raid buffed, our extra 200 isn't changing the mob hits too much.  I've gone back to DS in tank groups half the time but that's paltry DPS in comparison to what a rogue, wizard, or even ranger can do.
<br />

<br />
Resists are next to meaningless with many of the resist adjustments in Omens.  Even when I'm capping resists at 600 for the members of my group with POV, Omens spells are still landing.  When AEs are doing 3000 DD on impact and 500 a tick, I wish I could add DoT Shielding or Spell Shielding and actually be useful.  But alas, I cannot.  
<br />

<br />
I know I have many options.  There are fights where I can cure but AEs land so often I can't make a dent on more than 1 person.  So why raid with a bard who can keep 1 person clean when a cleric can RC a whole group?  Heh, why not add group cure song to the Bardic Wish List, er Top 10 List.
<br />

<br />
On some raids, group DA is my most useful song.
<br />

<br />
In Omens, I don't have the same usefulness I did in PoP.  h*ll, I don't have the same usefulness I did in NToV.
<br />

<br />
I'm talking about raid usefulness.  I don't question my usefulness in groups because my sheer flexibility makes me wanted above other classes.  I can pull well, I can slow and not pull aggro off a lesser geared tank, resists matter against trash (read: groupable xp mobs), and so does overhaste and spell damage.
<br />

<br />
So if you're spending most of your time grouping and raiding things outside the top tiers, I can understand how you shake your head at the current crop of &quot;whiny bards.&quot;  But know if you plan to progress, you'll be glad we're here whining for change that hopefully will be in place by the time you get there.
<br />

<br />
Calli</span></td>
