				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">swap your drum in as they land</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Before anyone rants right after... no, I have not parsed, but I don&#180;t think the game calculates which mod is in effect when the song lands, but when it is casted. I have swapped a drum after starting selo when starting to travel across zones, and I just go slower than if I swap the drum and start selo.
<br />

<br />
About grouping, still everyone likes to have a bard regardless, mainly because we offer mez, mana regen, slow, debuffs, pulling, and increased group effectiviness with our songs (heck, I even tanked 2 days ago at NW caves in WoS because there were no tanks available. I have LR10, ID10, Dodge 1 and +8% dodge mods. With 8300 HPs and 1600 AC, so I am not uber by any counts. The cleric was good though. We used root for agro, killed the named 4 times, got 3 shields and 1 pair of leather shoes. Had no medding downtime)
<br />

<br />
When raiding, it has been a long time, seems that way at least, since we had to leave peeps out of raid because we are maxed (we prolly raid with 50+ peeps at peak raid times, and like 30+ elsewhere). Still, I find mostly singing resists, manasong, 30% overhaste, PoV, etc. When I get bored I mez everything monks bring (Qvic pulls). OOW raids are lame and boring, thx SoE!
<br />

<br />
My number 1 SoE rant for that list would be:
<br />

<br />
Fix LFG time (for everyone)
<br />

<br />
Designing content where you need a cleric and a warrior or bust is dumb.
<br />

<br />
If server populations are low, people stay LFG for 30 minutes or so, before they log and move on to doing something else, making that server population even lower.
<br />

<br />
I think SoE needs to address the LFG downtime before they do anything else. And if that involves investing in AI, making mobs smarter so that we are no longer fighting singles, but group of mobs (hiting for less), and if that requires merging servers, so be it.
<br />

<br />
Yesterday, playing my chanter, Warrior was pulling in MPG, and due to repops we had 2 adds. Adds got locked, everything got killed and everyone said &quot;That was fun!&quot;. Too bad it only happened once in the 3 hours I was there. Why I am playing my bard all the time, and haven&#180;t played my chanter in 3 months. 
<br />

<br />
Can you imagine zones where single pulls are next to impossible, and there are roamers addingh left and right? Where you are fighting 3+ mobs at a time insetad of single pulls? Where pet ghetto mez is an option? Where a monk can tank? Where a ranger can snare kite the adds if too many? Where a druid or shaman can heal? I miss that most of all.
<br />

<br />
Disclaimer: I am aware druids and shamans can heal in MPG content, monks and berserkers can tank and so forth. I have done that many times with guildies QVic+ geared, but that is not your every day LFG Joe.</span></td>
