				<td colspan="2"><span>Conaden, I'm curious about your perspective.  I would love to be convinced that I'm just being negative, and if your guild is the top on Tholuxe, I'm sure you're in Anguish or near enough to have done a lot of the Omens raids.
<br />

<br />
My issue with PoV was not that everyone is capped.  It's that even with capped resists, the AEs are nearly unresistable.  Have you noticed a marked improvement singing PoV in say, Specialization?  I keep my logs on all the time and the only dent in my damage was based on my Spell Shielding mods, not from resists despite singing POV.  The trial is designed to require fast curing or else eat the AEs and bard songs don't make a difference even with capping everyone at 600.  I'm not saying every trial should require the same tactic and that tactic should be bard resists, but I do firmly feel like my usefulness has eroded on raids since PoP and I'm looking at concrete examples.
<br />

<br />
And I would never argue that bards can't amplify a group.  In fact, I pointed out that we're excellent in grouping situations for that reason.  But in a raid that is limited to 54 where DPS is crucial to success, adding bards is not as useful as adding another pure DPS class.  Because the raid limits have forced us to require classes to sit out and to design for optimum success, bards have been cut in favor of other classes.  I can't argue with the raid leader's decision because he's right.
<br />

<br />
I'm curious to hear where your perspective has come from since I'd rather adopt it, but I'm sceptical.
<br />

<br />
Calli</span></td>
