			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">But in a raid that is limited to 54 where DPS is crucial to success, adding bards is not as useful as adding another pure DPS class. Because the raid limits have forced us to require classes to sit out and to design for optimum success, bards have been cut in favor of other classes. I can't argue with the raid leader's decision because he's right. </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
I am glad your server has no low numbers issue, or that your guild is so well managed in terms of recruits that 60+ players show up for raiding on daily basis and your guild leader has to leave people out. My server is strugling population wise, we raided Qvic yesterday with 29 people (counting the boxed character for raid invites at Natimbi). I know it is holiday season and all, but I have never seen more than 50 peeps on any raid in the past few months (since EQ2/WoW). I know we are not the only ones experiencing this on our server, and prolly applies to a few servers as well.
<br />

<br />
In any case, you can easily make a case, since your guild has the luxury of choosing, that a bard in a group with 4 pure DPSers (rogues and wizzards) will easily grant more DPS than a 5th DPSer in said group. It is pretty straight forward:
<br />

<br />
30% + 4 = 120%
<br />

<br />
It can be argued that 30% focus on nukes is only the best case scenario and that often it is less, since 30% is chancy. If so, you can place bard with 4 rogues, that way the 120% is no longer a chance, but a sure thing.
<br />

<br />
The max number of bards I have seen raiding on my guild at any given time is 4. I would say the average is 2. As of late, with the holidays, it dropped to 1 or none.
<br />

<br />
I can&#180;t really imagine a guild not wanting at least 3 bards on a raid. 1 for Tanks group, 1 for manasong/resist, 1 for special DPS unit group. And if 3 bards is one too many cause between the 2 bards manasong and resists can be picked up, STILL bards are not inmune to dying on a raid encounter.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: STILL, you can say an extra 200 AC on tank AND an extra 250 ATK AND and extra 150 DS AND an extra 100+ CHA AND an extra 300 resists AND an extra 30% melee haste AND an extra 150 heal per tick will not make a difference. But when it DOES make the difference between lootz and wipes, to me it more than makes up for all the other times it didn&#180;t. It is a matter of seing the glass half full or half empty really.
<br />

<br />
Likewise, it can be said an extra DPSer will not make any difference either.</span></td>
