				<td colspan="2"><span>Every time I step into a group on a raid, I always get cool a bard.  I know I will save healers mana and amplify the damage output of my group members.  My guild is in Anguish and only killed Ture so far.  Thats due to some low numbers the past month.  We average around 40 people now per raid.  We kill King, Queen in RSS and do every single trial.  We also are in Tacvi.  As far as resists go, I resist alot.  I used to play VoV until I found out it had stacking issues.  Sometimes AEs will get through, but that extra 150 hps per tic adds up and you also have group DA to pulse.  Every time you pulse that DA song, you again just saved the healers mana.  Its especially useful for timed AEs.  Some fights require huge amounts of damage shields to win.  I won't say which ones, but thats the only way you'll win.  Guess whos needed for that?  Thats right... Anyway, bards are very useful and I wouldn't mind getting one more to make us 3 active bards to help us out.
<br />

<br />
Some other things to add here, not only do we buff people to make them more effective and save mana, but we are also very good debuffers and stack with shaman and chanter debuffs.  I am not the debuffer of my guild unless they aren't around.  Harmony of Sound and Chaos Chant stack.  Chaos Chant can get resisted though.  I do know that if they aren't played shamans and others will bitch about it.  If they have a hard time landing something, they will send you a tell and you'll hear about it.  Some mobs are still very resistant, even if you landed every debuff.
<br />

<br />
We are also pullers.  If we are outdoors, I usually get asked to pull.  I am still learning myself, but I have pulled Anguish and several other zones.  I'm excellent at pulling for groups but kinda suck for raid pulling atm.  Once I get some experience, I'm sure I'll be really good.
<br />

<br />
Conaden Darksong, 70 Bard
